Rlab: continuous spatial index

  1. [2 pts] What type of R object is sd_city? What coordinate reference system is used?

  • sd_city is SpatialPolygonsDataFrame

  • Coordinate reference system:

## [1] "+proj=lcc +lat_1=33.88333333333333 +lat_2=32.78333333333333 +lat_0=32.16666666666666 +lon_0=-116.25 +x_0=2000000.000101601 +y_0=500000.0001016002 +datum=NAD83 +units=us-ft +no_defs +ellps=GRS80 +towgs84=0,0,0"
  1. [1 pts] What does line 7 do?
  • Transform for map projection and datum transformation. sites_11 is the object to be transfer. And proj4string(sd_city) is the coordinate references CRS object.

  1. [2 pts] There are 9 NAs in sites$cl2_total. Why?
  • Because therere 9 sites that exist in sites_ll$site_ID but not water_testing$source
  1. [2 pts] Write your own code that creates a new variable called sites_sub that is just like sites, but has the 9 sample sites with NA values for cl2_total removed.
sites_sub <- sites$cl2_total[!is.na(sites$cl2_total)]
